    {
      "@id": "aiap:probe-gradient-descent-derivation",
      "@type": ["aiap:InterviewQuestion", "prov:Activity"],
      "aiap:questionCategory": "theoretical_foundations",
      "aiap:question": "Walk me through your logistic regression implementation. Derive the gradient descent update rule from the cross-entropy loss function. Include L2 regularization and explain the Bayesian interpretation.",
      "aiap:assessmentDimensions": ["ml_theory", "mathematical_rigor", "depth_vs_breadth"],
      "aiap:scoringRubric": {
        "@type": "aiap:ScoringRubric",
        "aiap:poor": "Cannot write update rule, confuses gradient descent with ascent, no understanding of loss function",
        "aiap:qualified": "Correct update: θ := θ - α * [(1/m)X^T(σ(Xθ) - y) + (λ/m)θ]. Explains sigmoid, cross-entropy, L2 penalty. Doesn't know Bayesian interpretation.",
        "aiap:excellent": "Full derivation: L(θ) = -(1/m)Σ[y*log(σ) + (1-y)*log(1-σ)] → ∂L/∂θ via chain rule → gradient = (1/m)X^T(σ(Xθ) - y). Adds L2: +(λ/2m)Σθ² → gradient becomes (1/m)X^T(σ(Xθ) - y) + (λ/m)θ. Update: θ := (1-αλ/m)θ - (α/m)X^T(σ(Xθ) - y). Bayesian: L2 ≡ MAP with Gaussian prior θ ~ N(0, 1/λ), log-posterior = log-likelihood - λΣθ²/2. Explains: weight decay (1-αλ/m) shrinks coefficients → generalization."
      }
    },
